The paper deals with the problem of generating all strongly stable matchings in a bipartite graph, which is a well-studied problem in the fields of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also presents algorithms for constructing a partial order representing all strongly stable matchings, which involves computational aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the distributive lattice structure of strongly stable matchings, which is a topic in the field of social choice theory (cs.SI).
